      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yep, that\u0027s the downside.  I guess the unspoken assumption of this CL is that no non-trivial client is doing this any more.  As you\u0027ve pointed out, there is a safety valve here... clients who want to continue to use mutable bitmaps (like Android) can use kNever_SkCopyPixelsMode to avoid the copy.\n\n(This _is_ the raster backend.)",
